            <span>Owner-Operator, Texas</span>
          </footer>
        </blockquote>

        <blockquote class="testimonial">
          <p>"Called at 7am needing a cert for a new broker. Had it in my email before I finished my coffee. That's the kind of service you can't find anywhere else."</p>
          <footer>
            <strong>Jennifer R.</strong>
            <span>Small Fleet Owner, Idaho</span>
          </footer>
        </blockquote>

        <blockquote class="testimonial">
          <p>"New authority, didn't know what I was doing. They walked me through every coverage, what it does, why I need it. No pressure, just straight answers."</p>
          <footer>
            <strong>David K.</strong>
            <span>New Authority, California</span>
          </footer>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUOTE FORM -->
  <section class="quote-form-section" id="quote">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="form-layout">
        <div class="form-info">
          <span class="section-num">04</span>
          <h2>Get a Quote</h2>
          <p>Fill out the form and we'll call you back. Usually same day, often within a couple hours.</p>

          <div class="form-benefits">
            <div class="benefit">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
              </svg>
              <span>No obligation quote</span>
            </div>
            <div class="benefit">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
              </svg>
              <span>We explain everything</span>
            </div>
            <div class="benefit">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
              </svg>
              <span>Same day response</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="form-alt">Or just call us: <a href="tel:208-800-0640">208-800-0640</a></p>
        </div>

        <form class="quote-form" action="https://formspree.io/f/YOUR_FORM_ID" method="POST">
          <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="name">Your Name</label>
              <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required placeholder="John Smith">
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="phone">Phone Number</label>
              <input type="tel" id="phone" name="phone" required placeholder="(555) 123-4567">
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="email">Email</label>
              <input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="john@example.com">
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="dot">DOT Number (if you have one)</label>
              <input type="text" id="dot" name="dot" placeholder="1234567">
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="status">Where are you in the process?</label>
            <select id="status" name="status">
              <option value="">Select one...</option>
              <option value="researching">Still researching / planning</option>
              <option value="getting-dot">Getting my DOT number now</option>
              <option value="new-authority">Just got my authority (< 6 months)</option>
              <option value="established">Established trucker, shopping for better service</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="message">Anything else we should know?</label>
            <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="3" placeholder="What you haul, how many trucks, questions you have..."></textarea>
          </div>

          <button type="submit" class="btn-submit">Get My Quote</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EXPANDED FAQ -->
  <section class="faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-layout">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <span class="section-num">05</span>
          <h2>Straight Answers to<br/><span class="gold">Common Questions</span></h2>
          <p class="faq-intro">No runaround. No jargon. Just the truth.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>How much does trucking insurance cost?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>It depends—and anyone who quotes you a price without asking questions is guessing. Your rate depends on your experience, your equipment, what you haul, where you operate, and your safety record. For a new authority with a newer truck, expect $12,000-$18,000/year for basic coverage. Experienced operators with clean records pay less. We'll give you a real quote based on your actual situation.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>Is your price lower than other agencies?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Honest answer: probably not much different. We all use the same carriers for new authorities—the price is basically the same everywhere. The difference is who picks up when you call, and whether they actually know the answer. We compete on service and expertise, not on being the cheapest.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>How fast can I get a quote?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Most quotes same day. If you have your info ready—DOT number, equipment details, driving history—often within a couple hours. We don't drag it out.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>I just got my authority. Where do I start?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Call us. Seriously—that's the first step. We'll walk you through what coverage you need, what the FMCSA requires, and how to get your filings done so you can start hauling. We help new authorities every day.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>What's the difference between an MC number and a DOT number?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Your DOT number is your safety registration with FMCSA—every commercial vehicle over 10,001 lbs needs one. Your MC (Motor Carrier) number is your operating authority—required if you're hauling freight for hire across state lines. You need both to operate legally as an interstate motor carrier.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>Do I need cargo insurance?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Legally? Not always. Practically? Yes. Most brokers and shippers won't work with you without cargo coverage. Standard is $100,000, but some commodities require more. We'll help you figure out what limits you actually need based on what you haul.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>What happens if I get a certificate request at 6am?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>You call us. We answer. We send the certificate. You get a confirmation. That's it. We understand that contracts don't wait—when you need a cert, you need it now.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>Can you help if I have accidents or violations on my record?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes. It affects your rates, but we work with carriers who specialize in non-standard risks. We'll be straight with you about what to expect and find you the best option given your history.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>What areas do you serve?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>We're based in Idaho and licensed in 40+ states. We serve owner-operators and small fleets nationwide. If you're hauling in the continental US, we can help.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span>How do I file a claim?</span>
              <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Call us first. We'll help you navigate the process, deal with the carrier, and make sure your claim gets handled properly. That's part of what you're paying us for.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT RMS -->
  <section class="about">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-layout">
        <div class="about-content">
          <span class="section-tag">About Us</span>
          <h2>Why RMS Exists</h2>

          <p class="about-lead">RMS Insurance was founded on a simple frustration: truckers deserve better.</p>

          <p>Trucking insurance isn't complicated—the industry just profits from keeping you confused. Agents use jargon to sound smart. Nobody explains anything. Everyone benefits when you don't quite understand what you're buying.</p>

          <p>We started RMS because that sticks in our craw. Our founder has a law degree and deep expertise in federal trucking regulations—the complexity that takes most people months to untangle, we can see through in minutes. And we believe that expertise should work for truckers, not against them.</p>

          <p>When you call RMS, things happen. Fast and right. You get straight answers in plain English. You understand what you're buying and why. And you have an expert in your corner who's actually on your side.</p>

          <p class="about-emphasis">That's what "finally, someone on your side" means.</p>
        </div>

